# working step of to do list

We use a list to store tasks.
Each task is saved as a dictionary
Checks if tasks list is empty.
If not, prints all tasks with their status (Done/Pending).
enumerate() is used to number the tasks starting from 1
Takes user input for a new task.
Adds it to the tasks list with "done": False (not yet completed).
First shows tasks.
Asks user for the task number.
Changes "done": False â†’ "done": True.
Handles errors (if user types wrong number or non-numeric input).
Shows tasks first.
Asks for task number to remove.
Uses pop() to delete task from the list.
Runs an infinite loop until user chooses Exit (5).
Displays menu and performs the chosen action.
